				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Your timer is the NMI, which occurs 60 times a second (or 50 for pal). So you should set a flag after your NMI routine that tells your main loop to do another frame. That looks like what you are doing as far as I can see. I'm sure there are other ways of doing it, but that's what I've been doing.
<br />
<br />There's only way to vary the "timer" is to just update every other frame, but I think that the best way to change the speed of objects is just to vary their velocity.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

