					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">67726e wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">However, couldn't I just start of the main loop with:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Main:<br />&nbsp; LDA Timer<br />&nbsp; BEQ Main</div></div>
<br />Ah, I see... Yeah, I guess you could to that without problems. It's just my preference to do the waiting at the end, because by that time the frame is already processed and the buffers with all PPU updates are already to be used when the NMI fires.
<br />
<br />If you wait at the start, or do all the logic inside the NMI, you have to deal with the case where during the first frame the NMI fires and there is no data to write to the PPU, becaue the frame hasn't been processed yet. Not that this is a problem at all, since we usually have a flag indicating if the updates should happen or not.</div>

